This an EXCLUSIVE COLLABORATION print created with my KWEST ONE for Designer Con 2013. 

We decided to create a print of our favorite DC COMICS One-Two Punch. The Caped Crusader & his loyal Wing Man. For this piece KWEST ONE drew his version of the Dark Knight while I drew my Modern take on the Boy Wonder. First dropped at D CON 2013, the remaining prints are now up for sale.

name: JESSE ('BLUE CRYSTAL' EDITION)
description:
11 x 17 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 25 PRINTS.

*This is a PRE-ORDER. Prints will not Ship for 2 weeks. (Sept. 21)

BREAKING BAD is coming to an end & there was no way I could create a WALT print & not create a print for his PARTNER in crime, JESSE PINKMAN. The high school drop-out, turned small time local METH COOK/ DEALER. Jesse was a kid with a "tough guy" attitude masking his inner pain of a broken family, caused by his own addictions. As the show progressed you laughed at Jesse, then felt sorry for him, then cheered for him to succeed as his 'heart' shined thru all his mess. Plus the dude dropped the word 'BITCH' constantly.
"Yeah, SCIENCE, BITCH!"

If you have never watched an episode, do yourself a favor and WATCH ALL OF THEM before you hear about the SERIES FINALE from EVERYONE.*

*You actually need to watch the show to get all the references in this Illustration.

name: SNIKT!
description:
8.5 x 11 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 50 PRINTS.

At the beginning of 2013, I attempted the SKETCH A DAY challenge which I called #TTDOODLES. I admittedly fell off the wagon but will soon be getting back up on that drawing horse. To help celebrate me getting back to drawing & the release of THE WOLVERINE (which BTW was a GOOD MOVIE) I am releasing a LIMITED EDITION print of my DAY #5 TT DOODLE. Everyone's favorite CANUCK with CLAWS, but in COLOR!

If you want to see the original drawing & more of my art, hit up my IG: @tracytubera #TTDOODLES

name: EVIL RYU
description:
8.5 x 11 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 25 PRINTS.

At SDCC 2013 my TRACY TUBERA x BAIT x STREET FIGHTER T-SHIRT finally dropped. BAIT & CAPCOM both liked my RYU from my 'WAY OF THE DRAGON FIST' print and asked if I would like to put my art on a t-shirt. OF COURSE I said "YES!" 

The regular version of the shirt is 'NORMAL' RYU but for SDCC 13 BAIT made an EVIL RYU version. To help celebrate this Comic Con exclusive, I created a print to match the shirt. I sold this print during my signing at the BAIT booth, and these are the last remaining prints. Get one while they last.

SHORYUKEN!

name: MARS JUMPMAN
description:
8.5 x 11 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 50 PRINTS.

The AIR JORDAN 3's are hands down my favorite Jordans (much like most people) The old Spike Lee/ Mars Blackmon Air Jordan commercials were such a perfect fit for this line of bold, "in your face" Bball shoes. MARS said it best, "Is it the shoes? Is it the shoes? Is it the shoes?....It's gotta be the shoes." Not only do Jordans mean JORDAN, but to me the early Jordans, especially the 3's, also mean MARS BLACKMON. So, this is my take on the famous JUMPMAN logo but with a bit of MARS added in. He is "The BEST on MARS."

name: ROSHE RUNNING (GREY/TEAL EDITION)
description:
8.5 x 11 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 50 PRINTS.

Another SNEAKER HEAD ART drop! Straight from my instagram "A Sketch a Day for a Year" Series #ttdoodles.

The ROSHE RUN is hands down one of the most COMFORTABLE SHOES I HAVE EVER OWNED! Besides the comfort (It's like walking on Clouds of Marshmallows) the design of the shoe is so simple & clean. Nike Designer Dylan Raasch, took inspiration from his own life of practicing meditation & took that mentality of ZEN & SIMPLICITY & applied them to the shoe. The shoe is even named after the title given to a ZEN MASTER, "ROSHI". For legal reasons the spelling had to be changed, but still pronounced the same.

For this print I again took the nickname of the shoe, in this case the shoe's ACTUAL name and created an illustration based on the name & ZEN CALLIGRAPHY. The shoe is called the ROSHE RUN, I drew a picture of a ROSHI RUNNING...."ROSHE RUNNING"....MIND BLOWN!

This EDITION of the print is based on one of the original colorways released for the shoe, GREY/ TEAL

MORE SNEAKER ART TO COME!

name: WAY OF THE DRAGON FIST
description:
13 x 19 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed & numbered. LIMITED TO ONLY 25 PRINTS.

Here is my Illustration for the 25th Anniversary STREET FIGHTER II Art Show at BAIT presented by CAPCOM & TSUNAMI SYNDICATE. 

The underline theme of the illustration is the YIN YANG. The constant balance of two sides to make ONE whole. RYU & KEN have two different approaches towards their martial arts training and lifestyle, but they are forever linked to each other by their training & drive to become the worlds best Martial Artist. Also they have the most AWESOMEST MARTIAL ARTS BROMANCE. 

If you look closely to the print you will see multiple hidden signs of the TAO & if you look a bit harder you will also see multiple homages to the man, BRUCE LEE. 

Also the print can be hung with either RYU facing UP or KEN facing up. You choose your fighter.

SHORYUKEN!!!!!

name: DARYL 'RED' EDITION
description:
11 x 17 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 100 PRINTS.

AMC's THE WALKING DEAD is AMAZEBALLS! One of my favorite TV shows on air today. I was a fan of the show & then started reading the comic after. Both are GREAT & I love how you can enjoy & still be surprised by what happens in each version without ruining any story plots for yourself.

DARYL DIXON is the MAN! A BAD ASS "take no sh!t from no one" type of character that started out as a Loner & then soon became a a valuable part of the group. This is my illustration of the man, the myth, the DARYL!

This version of the print shows Daryl in FULL ZOMBIE/WALKER/ROAMER KILLING COLOR. They better not kill off Daryl or the WORLD will RIOT!

name: DARYL 'COMIC BOOK' EDITION
description:

Fans of the comic & show know that Daryl was not originally from the comic but created solely for the show. This version of the print puts Daryl Dixon in the WALKING DEAD comic book world & pays homage to the comic's, now distinct BLACK & WHITE look. Add a splash of RED for the blood & gore of ZOMBIE/WALKER/ROAMER killing and you got yourself a B.A.M.F. DARYL PRINT.

name: BAD ASS MEGA MAN
description:
8.5 x 11 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 50 PRINTS.

I was honored to have my version of BAD BOX ART MEGA MAN (the famed US Box art of MEGA MAN. It's pretty UGLY. See pic of the BOX ART below) chosen to be in the MEGA MAN TRIBUTE LIMITED EDITION HARDCOVER. I took the Original BAD BOX ART MEGA MAN concept and flipped it so he looked more in line with the actual look of MEGA MAN. I named him BAD ASS MEGA MAN

The MEGA MAN TRIBUTE book was first sold at San Diego Comic-Con 2010 at the UDON booth, but you can still find the book online or at your local Comic Book shop. I am finally releasing prints of my Illustration. If you are a fan of the blue dude with a blaster for an arm, pick up the book & this PRINT! MEGA! MEGA!

name: TUX IN THE HAT
description:
13 x 19 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 10 PRINTS. 

This is a very special print that I created for my Triplet boys. Their nursery is decorated in a "CAT IN THE HAT" theme, so I wanted to draw something special for them. I drew each boy as THING 1, THING 2, & THING 3, and replaced the CAT with my French Bulldog, TUX.

I also picked out one of my favorite Dr. Seuss quotes, that I think fits my boys perfectly. "Why fit in, when you were born to stand out!"

If you have Triplet boys, a French Bulldog, or just love Dr. Seuss, this print is for you :)

name: WALT A/P PRINTS
description:
11 x 17 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, has "A/P" written in the LEFT BOTTOM CORNER, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LESS then 10 PRINTS for each EDITION.

Here they are. My remaining batch of ARTIST PROOF prints from D CON. This is it. If you missed out on the original run of all 3 WALT PRINTS, here is your chance to get one or one of each.

Again, these are from my personal stash of A/Ps so they are NOT NUMBERED and there are only less than 10 of each EDITION.

Get'em while they are hot!

name: AIR WOLF
description:
8.5 x 11 PRINT on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed, numbered, & HAND EMBOSSED with my DOUBLE T logo. LIMITED TO ONLY 50 PRINTS.

This a print of my original piece for the JUST DOIN IT show at Dragatomi with KANO. All my pieces were plays off nicknames for popular sneakers. For this print I changed up the colors from the OG piece.

My holy grail of sneakers would have to be the NIKE AIR MAGS. I love me some BACK TO THE FUTURE! I wanted to do another AIR MAG illustration (my first one being 'FUTURE BOY'), but didn't want to do another MARTY McFLY character design. Sooooo, I decided to mash together 2 of MJF's best movies. 'BTTF 2' & TEEN WOLF= AIR WOLF.

If you ever wondered what a Werewolf would look like wearing Air Mags and riding a hoverboard, then look NO further....DICKNOSE.

This an EXCLUSIVE COLLABORATION print created with my BESTEST BUD, KWEST ONE for Designer Con 2012. 

We wanted to do a print based on one of our favorite childhood cartoons, VOLTRON the DEFENDER of the UNIVERSE. Chito AKA KWEST ONE came up the idea to half the character and to create each side in our own individual art style. He came up with STEAM PUNK VOLTRON & I came up with a more simplistic "Mega Man"-like VOLTRON. BOOM! MIND BLOWN!

Walt's DRUG LORD alter ego. This print puts HEISENBERG out in front in FULL COLOR, much like how WALT is becoming more 'HEISENBERG' than 'WALT' on the show.

*This is a PRE-ORDER. The prints will not be available for 2 weeks. (Sept. 21)

name: WALT ('BLUE CRYSTAL' EDITION)
description:

IMO BREAKING BAD is the BEST TV show on air right now! With it's last season half way thru I had to draw a picture of the main character, WALTER WHITE. WALTER is one of the most complex characters ever created for a TV show. A chemistry teacher with terminal cancer turned into a METH COOK/ DRUG LORD. From the start of the show you felt bad for him, then as seasons went on you rooted for him, and now as the show comes to an end you fear him. If you have never watched an episode, do yourself a favor and WATCH ALL OF THEM.*

*You actually need to watch the show to get all the references in the Illustration.

AMERICA F* YEAH!- It's everyone's favorite SUPER SOLDIER, CAPTAIN AMERICA, ready to stomp out all who oppose FREEDOM! That 'A' on his helmet doesn't stand for FRANCE! (An ULTIMATES quote. NERD TALK!)

name: HOMEMADE HERO & TUX
description:

Based on a painting I did a few years back, HOMEMADE HERO RETURNS! But this time he brought backup..TUX the FRENCH BULLDOG! As a kid I grew up on comic books & cartoons. I would love to grab the towel from the bathroom tie it around my neck, wear my UNDER-ROOS on the outside of my shorts & pretend to be my favorite super hero. HOMEMADE HERO represents that special time of my childhood when my imagination was my favorite toy. 

I created this print EXCLUSIVELY for D CON 2011 & it sold well, I only have a few left over so here is your chance to snag one if you couldn't make it out to the show.

name: FUTURE BOY
description:
11 x 17 Print on ARCHIVAL WATERCOLOR PAPER Each Print is signed & numbered. LIMITED TO ONLY 25 PRINTS.

GREAT SCOTT! When NIKE announced the release of the AIR MAGS I went APE SH#T! Not only am I a huge SNEAKER HEAD, but I am a HUGE BACK TO THE FUTURE NUT! I've always dreamed about owning my own pair of power lacing AIR MAGS. Unfortunately the prices were HEAVY & many SNEAKER HEADS/ BTTF fans were left with feet not power laced up (even though the AIR MAGS 2011 didn't POWER LACE, WTF?)

Have no fear, my fellow AIR MAG worshipers. If you couldn't get your hands on a pair of AIR MAGS why not get a piece of art celebrating the infamous sneaks & the man who made them HOT in the FUTURE for us in the past...MARTY McFLY! This LIMITED EDITION print showcases the exact FIT that MARTY wore when he traveled to the FUTURE ,PLUS Doc Brown's METAL SHADES for extra SWAG!

If you LOVE the AIR MAGS & BACK TO THE FUTURE, then you will love this PRINT! This print is your DENSITY...I mean DESTINY.

name: 10- DOH SUPER DOUBLE NINJA BATTLE BROS.
description:
Say hello to SUPER DOUBLE NINJA BATTLE BROS. The most RARE 10-DOH game ever created. I took everyone's FAVORITE Side Scrolling games & MASHED'EM UP into one BAD ASS BRAWLER! SDNBB is the story of 2 Brothers out to bring JUSTICE to the streets. These Brothers are PLUMBERS by day, NINJAS by night, & ALWAYS BATTLE for BLOOD!

This was my design for SERIES 1 of 10-DOH! 10-Doh! Is the first figure from the So Analog line by Squid Kids Ink. The body is made of ABS with the hands and feet are made of PVC. Each 10-Doh! figure stands 7" tall. There were only 300 made of my design.

Each figure is signed on the back & shipped in it's original packaging. If cartridge does not work when received, blow into the bottom of it, & press reset multiple times on your console :) (Cartridges DO NOT really work)

name: KOBE VI PRINTS
description:
11 x 17 Print on Archival Velvet Finish Paper. Each print is signed & numbered. LIMITED TO ONLY 24 PRINTS. (Each PRINT is $30.00)

In homage to the GREATEST BALLER IN THE WORLD, I created an Illustration celebrating the numerous colorways that came out for his 6th signature shoe. A print to match every HOT colorway that dropped. 

The GRINCHS- Although they were officially  part of the "STOP LIGHT SERIES", the Interweb dubbed them "THE GRINCHS." I had to go with that nick name, because these kicks stole money from my wallet.

The DEL SOLS- The standard colorway in the KOBE shoe line, but for the VI's, ones that really show off the BLACK MAMBA theme.

The CONCORDS- This colorway has unofficially become KOBE's Home game kicks. A clean looking shoe with the right amount of a pop color. BAM!

The EAST LA's-  Once thought to be Kobe's ASG shoe, but in fact they were not. They were the first shoe in a SERIES of LA CITY themed KICKS. 3 Shoes all representing 3 different locales of Southern Cali. EAST LOS represent! ODELAY!

The HOLLYWOOD 3Ds- The Second shoe released from the LA CITY SERIES. This shoe is my favorite! The concept behind it is a play off of the Hollywood trend of 3D movies. What better way to celebrate this shoe, but with a 3D PRINT! Yup, the print is 3D & COMES WITH the OLD SCHOOL 3D glasses to enjoy it in all it's tripiness! WHOAAAAAA! KOBE JUMPS OFF THE PRINT!

The HOLLYWOOD 3Ds (NORMAL)- Same as the actual 3D print, but not an ANAGLYPH (meaning... NOT 3D)

The OC SUNSETS- The Third & final shoe released from the LA CITY SERIES. This shoe celebrates the beautiful Beaches of the OC & where Kobe lives. Luckily you don't have to be OC RICH to purchase this print.

The ALL STARS-  The actual ALL STAR SHOES that Kobe wore during the 2011 ALL STAR Game in LA. These bad boys are a sick RED & BLACK color combo. My 2 favorite colors!

The GLASS BLUES- These were the most colorful pair of KOBE VI's to drop. They remind me of the NIKE SB SKATE OR DIE's & that's probably the reason why I LOVE'EM! The bright colors, the "glass"/ clear bottom soles these kicks have it all! 

The CHINAS- These are a prime example of how KOBE is a GLOBAL SUPERSTAR. China gets their own colorway of these dope kicks! Sure the only difference between the US release & the Asia release are some lace locks & a crazy box, but c'mon!...There ain't no USA colorway.... At least not yet. China loves them some KOBE BRYANT, & they love them some KOBE SHOES! A billion peeps with great taste.
